item.title: Delphine add a quote by Stephen Fry
item.description: "It's not all bad. Heightened self-consciousness, apartness, an inability to join in, physical shame and self-loathing—they are not all bad. Those devils have been my angels. Without them I would never have disappeared into language, literature, the mind, laughter and all the mad intensities that made and unmade me." -- Stephen Fry

item.title: Delphine add a quote by D.D. Barant
item.description: "I've got a bad case of the 3:00 am guilts - you know, when you lie in bed awake and replay all those things you didn't do right? Because, as we all know, nothing solves insomnia like a nice warm glass of regret, depression and self-loathing." -- D.D. Barant

item.title: Delphine add a quote by Sam Pink
item.description: "My ideal date would involve painful silence. My ideal date wouldn't involve me." -- Sam Pink

item.title: Delphine add a quote by Eleanor Roosevelt

item.title: Delphine add a quote by Maurice Switzer
